This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a defense mechanism for deep neural networks. It also involves the evaluation of the proposed method through experiments, which is a common practice in the field of machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks and proposes a defense mechanism to mitigate such attacks. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another likely category as deep neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks, and the proposed defense mechanism aims to improve the robustness of such networks against adversarial attacks. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the vulnerability of deep neural networks, which is a common concern in the field of AI. 

Finally, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant as the paper proposes a defense mechanism to protect neural networks, which are a type of control system.
